---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Demo - SkanPay"
  description="See how BeamCash demonstrates the QR checkout workflow SkanPay wants merchants, payment partners, and future financial partners to understand."
  activePath="/beamcash-demo/"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Demo</p>
    <h1>BeamCash shows the QR checkout experience in motion</h1>
    <p>
      A focused product demo for explaining seller setup, customer approval, and the SkanPay gateway vision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section demo-overview">
    <div class="demo-overview-copy">
      <img class="beamcash-wordmark" src="/beamcash/beamcash-wordmark.svg" alt="BeamCash" />
      <p class="eyebrow">Purpose</p>
      <h2>A controlled demo, not the final gateway product</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        BeamCash makes the SkanPay concept tangible. It shows how a merchant-facing QR screen and a customer-facing checkout screen can work together before deeper partner-specific requirements are discussed.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside class="demo-brief" aria-label="Demo boundaries">
      <div>
        <span>Demo scope</span>
        <strong>Seller QR setup and buyer checkout</strong>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>SkanPay role</span>
        <strong>Gateway and checkout coordination model</strong>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>Boundary</span>
        <strong>Demo only. No live payment processing.</strong>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section demo-stage-band">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Product proof</p>
        <h2>Two screens, one checkout conversation</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        The seller needs a readable QR checkout surface. The buyer needs a familiar review-and-pay flow.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="demo-stage">
      <figure class="phone-shot seller-shot">
        <img src="/beamcash/beamcash-seller-dashboard-mobile.png" alt="BeamCash seller dashboard with QR code and readiness status" />
        <figcaption>
          <span>Seller view</span>
          QR code, readiness state, and recent activity in one merchant surface.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="demo-connector" aria-hidden="true">
        <span>Scan</span>
        <strong>→</strong>
        <span>Approve</span>
      </div>
      <figure class="phone-shot buyer-shot">
        <img src="/beamcash/beamcash-buyer-checkout-mobile.png" alt="BeamCash buyer checkout screen with merchant profile and payment amount" />
        <figcaption>
          <span>Buyer view</span>
          Merchant review, amount entry, and a familiar checkout action.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section demo-evidence">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What it proves</p>
        <h2>BeamCash gives SkanPay a concrete reference</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        The point is not to claim live processing. The point is to make the checkout handoff visible.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="evidence-grid">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Merchant side is understandable</h3>
        <p>Staff can see the QR surface and the activity context without learning a complicated workflow.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Customer side is familiar</h3>
        <p>The buyer reviews who they are paying and confirms through a checkout-like flow.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Partner discussions get specific</h3>
        <p>The demo creates a shared reference for gateway, wallet, loyalty, and redemption conversations.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Next step</p>
      <h2>Use the demo to guide the integration conversation.</h2>
      <p>Share the merchant, wallet, or partner flow you want to evaluate.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="button secondary" href="/contact/">Request a Conversation</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
